An Ironman triathlon is a long-distance triathlon race that consists of a 2.4-mile (3.86 km) swim, a 112-mile (180.25 km) bike ride, and a 26.2-mile (42.20 km) run. The total distance covered in an Ironman triathlon is 140.6 miles (226.3 km). The race is known for its grueling physical demands and is considered one of the most challenging endurance events in the world.